title: Robber’s Roost Jerky Recalls Beef and Pork Jerky Product Due to Possible Listeria Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, April 1, 2015 Robbers Roost Jerky, an Ellensburg, Wash., establishment, is recalling approximately 4 pounds of ready-to-eat smoked beef and pork pepper stick jerky product that may be contaminated with Listeria monocytogenes, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced...
